      "appCustomProperties": {
        "state": "engineered",
        "edbb": {
          "role": "trading",
          "intro": "The whole build ladder on one screen. Initial is a cheap buy-only bulk starter; A-Rated is the best buy-only bulk-and-range fit; Engineered trims weight for laden range without losing a single cargo rack. Plans and costs follow in sections 07-09.",
          "callout": {
            "label": "The cargo-vs-range trade",
            "text": "Every cargo rack you swap for a shield or Guardian booster costs tonnage but buys survivability or range. A light bi-weave shield and the Guardian FSD booster are worth their slots; the booster is materials, not credits, and is the single highest-impact item on the hull."
          },
          "notes": {
            "TinyHardpoint1": "One shield booster is plenty on a hauler; Heavy Duty multiplies the light bi-weave's MJ so an interdiction is survivable, not fatal.",
            "TinyHardpoint2": "Optional / low-priority — Ammo Capacity adds heat-sink charges. Dumps heat for silent running and Thermal-Vent resets.",
            "TinyHardpoint3": "Optional / low-priority — Ammo Capacity adds rounds. Point Defence shoots down incoming missiles and torpedoes.",
            "PowerPlant": "6A gives power headroom for the shield, booster and FSD; Low Emissions runs it cool and quiet, Thermal Spread bleeds the rest.",
            "MainEngines": "Left at 7D to save mass and credits, you are not dogfighting; Clean Drive Tuning keeps it cool with a touch of boost speed to escape.",
            "FrameShiftDrive": "The one roll that matters on a trader: 6A + Increased Range + Mass Manager buys back the range every laden cargo rack costs you.",
            "LifeSupport": "D-rate to save mass, Lightweight trims more; life support has no experimental effect.",
            "PowerDistributor": "Charge Enhanced raises the weapon, engine and system capacitors.",
            "Radar": "Drop to D and go Lightweight; a hauler needs no sensor range, so save the mass for jump range.",
            "FuelTank": "Stock 6C tank pairs with the scoop on long hauls; fuel capacity is fixed and cannot be engineered.",
            "Slot01_Size8": "Optional — Expanded Capacity adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Holds cargo.",
            "Slot02_Size8": "Optional — Expanded Capacity adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Holds cargo.",
            "Slot03_Size7": "Optional — Expanded Capacity adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Holds cargo.",
            "Slot04_Size6": "Light bi-weave shield (C-rated only) regenerates fast and is cheap to power; Enhanced Low Power keeps its draw tiny so power stays free for the FSD.",
            "Slot05_Size5": "Optional — Expanded Capacity adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Holds cargo.",
            "Slot06_Size4": "Guardian FSD Booster claws back the jump range the cargo costs you; the highest-impact item on the ship and not engineerable.",
            "Slot07_Size4": "Optional — Expanded Capacity adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Holds cargo.",
            "Slot08_Size3": "Optional — Expanded Capacity adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Holds cargo.",
